Etymology. This species is dedicated to the memory of Paulo Secchin Young, a gifted taxonomist with a great knowledge of marine biology and a great collector with profound concerns for biodiversity and conservation issues, along with a leader in the broad sense with indefatigable passion for his work (
Serejo & Paiva, 2006
). He encouraged the first author (KCS) to pursue taxonomic studies of tanaids with the loan of material for post–graduate studies.
